entries.femaleVariant: And Blue Moon told me at rehearsal they haven't had this quality sound in a long time. No artefacts, no reverb.
Passes?
[Show pass] Right here.
In ya go.
Rather get to know you.
Everybody claims to know the stars.
Hm. Think I'd rather get to know you better.
You're all right, kitten. What's your name?
[Stand] Some other time.
Another time.
All right, I'm a gentleman, I won't make you. You'll change your mind, though.

entries.maleVariant: Chill chicks.

entries.femaleVariant: They'll be yours. I'll help.
Buy you a beer.
Those cracks'll be yours, I got you.

entries.maleVariant: Be my wingman, huh?

entries.femaleVariant: Over here – beer for my choom.

entries.maleVariant: Thanks, man. I'm fuckin' beat. Fifteen goddamn hours to set that shit up.
And then we had to figure out those fuckin' winch encoders with the Japanese, 'cause naturally they got their own fuckin' algorithms... Showbiz? Shitbiz, tellin' ya.

entries.femaleVariant: Yeah, gettin' out after this gig for good.
entries.maleVariant: Yeah, gettin' out after this gig, for good.

entries.femaleVariant: Prolly gonna send Ronnie over to Europe.
Fucking Japanese markers.
He tell 'em you were pregnant?
Sure, but he can't opt out, we're still payin' off his implants.
So where's your badge?
Find 'em?
Well, got 'em?
Know the girls, really?
[Stand] Gotta go.

entries.maleVariant: Cool, cool. So after, grab a beer and get to work on the girls...?

entries.femaleVariant: G'luck. Gotta run.
How's it looking? Everything ready?
How's it lookin' pre-show? Everything in order?
Yeah... Had some hiccups with the sound, little starlets wanted their own matrixes, some custom-made Japanese shit.
Yeah, "sound system"... Must be one of those smart vocoders. Do the whole damn job for 'em.
We're crew.
Chill. We'll get our passes, be right back.
Choom, come on, help us out. Left 'em inside.
entries.maleVariant: Choom, come on, help us out. We left 'em inside.

entries.femaleVariant: Nah, can't. Try the main door, they'll check the list.
Yeah, but by that time the holoprojectors'll be on and outta whack. I'll have to recalibrate, and no way this show starts on time.
And then it's sayonara, choom. You're out, 'cause ain't no way we're takin' the fall.
Fuck. Alright, go. Staple 'em to your fuckin' foreheads next time, will ya?
"Recalibrate holoprojectors." How you even know shit like that?
Thanks, pal. Just saved the show.
entries.maleVariant: Thanks, pal. You just saved the show.

entries.femaleVariant: Past life. Worked backstage for G-Hung for a time, learned some things. Finally came in handy today.
Crew passes, then.
Forgot 'em, you know how it is.
No passes, no passage.
So I says to her, I know a way you can thank me after, heh...
And what'd Blue Moon say?
Told me to do my fucking job and set up the tech. But you know – with all that make-up on, hard to say what they're really thinking.
You know the girls, like, personally?
Hear 'bout that truck? Full of the girls' gear? All blew up?
entries.maleVariant: Ya hear about that truck? Full of the girls' gear? All blew up?

entries.femaleVariant: Sure did. Guy at the bottom gets the short end of the stick always.
Girls aren't exactly at the bottom.
No, I'm talkin' about the drivers. Got fired, both. For "leaving the scene," not bein' there give the cops information.
Musta been a pain for the girls, though. Gear destroyed, gig delayed. Think it mighta been someone sendin' a message?
Nah. Shit was insured. Prolly get more scratch outta this than that junk was worth.
Besides, what's some truck to them? Couldn't give a shit, prolly didn't even know about it. What their manager's for, ain't it?
Not right now.
Know what? Fuck off.
entries.maleVariant: Y'know what? Fuck off.

entries.femaleVariant: Look, everybody says they know so-and-so. Always turns out they don't know shit.
V. You?
Donnie. But you can call me "D".
How about we get outta here for a few minutes? Maybe even a few more, if you're lucky?
[Stand] Know what? Fuck off.
Maybe later.
Ooooh...
If not now, when, hon? Be the end of the world and you'll still be givin' me maybes.
Blue Moon, Purple Force, Red Menace...
Whole world can rattle that off.
entries.maleVariant: The whole world can rattle that off.

entries.femaleVariant: True... but look. They ain't here, you are. How 'bout we focus on you, huh?
Nice eyes you got. Kiroshi?
Three choombas. You, me and my man, Ke-- Ken. Who could resist?

entries.maleVariant: Y'know what? Not s'posed to like the new guys, right? But what the fuck. You're all right.
Hell yeah, man. Run far as you can from this fuckin' mess. From these... stars an' shit.

entries.femaleVariant: We're crew.
Chill.
Let us in or lose your job.
[Sit] Hey.
You hear about that truck fire?
Yeah, go.
Hey.
Need a pass to the dressing rooms.
entries.maleVariant: I need a pass to the dressing rooms.

entries.femaleVariant: Gotta get a pass to the dressing rooms.
Ahh... Gotta figure something out quick. Those cunts're gonna start singin' soon.
Hah, club gigs. Amateur hour. They were any good, they'd be fillin' stadiums.
Amen, brother.
Which Crack you like best?
Which Crack's your fave?

entries.maleVariant: Choom, how can you possibly choose?! Blue Moon? Or no, wait – Purple Force.
Yep... gonna puke.

entries.femaleVariant: Mhm.
[Sit] This spot free?
Is this spot free? Mind if I...?
Good thing they're not filling stadiums just yet.
Least it's here and not at one of your sold-out stadiums. Woulda had to contend with huscle, medias, fuckin' NCPD drones, NetWatch...
entries.maleVariant: Well, least it's here and not at one of your sold-out stadiums. Woulda had to contend with huscle, medias, fuckin' NCPD drones, NetWatch...

entries.femaleVariant: Don't get smart on me. Look for a way backstage.
Guy there. Roadie. So he's done with his job for now. He's gonna wanna drink, get himself some strange.
Uh-huh. So he won't be needin' that card.
Distract him. I'll grab the pass.
Aw, it's not that bad. They locked mine up when Diego was barely one. Look how he turned out without a father.
Heh, hon, not judgin', but Diego's mannin' corners for the 'Tinos...
He's earning his own eddies. I don't know what you're talking about.
How the fuck am I supposed to know what goes where.
That's it, fuck it. I'm going back to installing feed cables.
Gotta get backstage.
Boys couldn't figure out how link it all up. Dunno, apparently it's all good now.

entries.maleVariant: Looks so innocent, but soon as she starts talkin' dirty on stage, even without the AudioVox, she got me standin' right to attention!
Hey.

entries.femaleVariant: Heyyyy there. How you doin'?

entries.maleVariant: Sure. Free country, ain't it?

entries.femaleVariant: It's got your name on it.

entries.maleVariant: Like I was banging 'em, choom.

entries.femaleVariant: Wanna meet 'em, hon? I can set it up. No problem.
